cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.TL, cs.SE, cs.FL 

This paper deals with the design and metatheory of a gradual language with explicit parametric polymorphism, which involves type systems and programming languages. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses relational parametricity, which falls under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also mentions the Abstracting Gradual Typing methodology, which is related to type theory and falls under cs.TL (Type Theory and Logic). The paper also discusses the handling of type instantiations, which is related to software engineering and falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses gradual free theorems, which is related to formal languages and falls under cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
